Brazil ' s Sabesp plans $ 200 million Eurobond - paper . Sao Paulo state ' s sewage company Sabesp plans to launch a $ 200 million Eurobond by June , the Financial Times reported on Wednesday . It would use the funds to replace existing debt with cheaper funding , the paper said , quoting Sabesp representative Claudio Gaiarsa . Sabesp was also considering sub - concessions to foreign water companies to raise capital , the paper said . Sabesp operates concessions granted by Sao Paulo ' s municipalities , and in December 1996 provided water and sewage services to 22 million people , nearly 60 percent of Sao Paulo state ' s population , in 329 municipalities . - - Aline van Duyn , London Newsroom + 44 171 542 7748 
